mesquite.lib.characters

Class CharacterState

  • java.lang.Object
    • mesquite.lib.characters.CharacterState
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CategoricalState, ContinuousState, MeristicState

    public abstract class CharacterState
extends java.lang.Object
    An abstraction of a state of a character to allow categorical, continuous and other subclasses.

      • isImpossible

        public abstract boolean isImpossible()
        returns whether value is valid or not. Impossible is a special value for each character type, and should be used to indicate a state is invalid.
